A hookah is an instrument used for smoking shisha, or flavored tobacco. Hookahs resemble bongs. They are made from ceramics, glass and sometimes brass.

Hookahs come in 3 different distinct styles, Egyptian, Arabic, and Syrian.

They come in all different sizes, to very small mini hookahs for just one person, or for people to pass. Or giant hookahs that have 3 or more hoses that sit on the ground and the users sit in a circle around it.